        <updateDate>2015-01-27T16:44:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>School Lunch Improvements for Children's Education Act or the SLICE Act - Authorizes the Secretary of Agriculture (USDA) to implement an interim or final rule regarding the school lunch and child nutrition programs that: (1) requires the crediting of tomato paste and puree as a vegetable serving based on the volume of tomato paste or puree served, (2) implements science-based sodium reduction targets, and (3) establishes a whole grain requirement.</p> <UL> </UL> <BR>]]></text>
      </summary>
